.TH "nla_policy_len" 9 "nla_policy_len" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nla_policy_len \- Determin the max. length of a policy
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nla_policy_len
.BI "(const struct nla_policy *p "  ","
.BI "int n "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "p" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "n" 12
number of policies
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Determines the max. length of the policy.  It is currently used
to allocated Netlink buffers roughly the size of the actual
message.

Returns 0 on success or a negative error code.
